  "prompt": "I confessed my feelings to my crush and she became very angry. What should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about that difficult experience. Here are a few steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Give Her Space:** Sometimes people need time to process unexpected information. Respect her space and time to think.\n\n2. **Reflect on the Situation:** Try to understand her perspective and consider if there was anything in your approach or timing that may have led to her reaction.\n\n3. **Communicate Openly:** When the time feels right, reach out in a calm and respectful manner. You could apologize if you feel it's necessary, or simply explain your intentions and feelings more clearly. \n\n4. **Set Boundaries:** It might be helpful to clarify your relationship moving forward. Let her know that you value her boundaries and are willing to respect them.\n\n5. **Focus on Yourself:** Take care of your own emotional needs and well-being. Confessing feelings can be vulnerable, so it's important to practice self-care.\n\n6. **Consider Professional Help:** If you're struggling with the emotional impact, speaking with a therapist or counselor could provide support and guidance.\n\nRemember, communication and understanding are key in any relationship. Be patient and kind to both yourself and your crush as you navigate this situation.",
